    "description": "<p class=\"Body-Foundation\">When you have a few minutes of silence to focus, you can <strong>mark a Stress</strong> to change the appearance of all willing creatures within Close range. Their new forms must share a general body structure and size, and can be somebody or something you’ve seen before or entirely fabricated. A disguised creature has advantage on Presence Rolls to avoid scrutiny.</p><p class=\"Body-Foundation\">Activate a Countdown (8). It ticks down as a consequence the GM chooses. When it triggers, the disguise drops.</p>",
